## 5) Initialize Git, commit, and push (local â†’ GitHub)

If you created repo via GitHub web UI and did NOT initialize with README, follow these steps:

```bash
# from inside ai-smart-wearable/
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit: project skeleton"
# add remote (copy the URL from your GitHub repo page)
git remote add origin https://github.com/<your-username>/ai-smart-wearable.git
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main
git pull origin main --allow-unrelated-histories
# resolve conflicts if any, then:
git push -u origin main
